er of the Sphere</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#330000>(11/16/01 3:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub51.ezboard.com/fsphereofhonour58352frm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Life or Death of a Bard</span><hr size=1> Rhapsodey sits Quietly at her fire in the Eastern Karranas her Dark blue armor lays beside her lovingly polished and prepared to be equipped in a moments notice.  She is humming Softly and seems to be writing in a tattered book. The gentle touch of clouding magic can be felt in the area.<br>
<br>
<br>
I successfully tracked down the scribe that has been writing Ballads of the Druid Nellen.  I confronted him this day Demanding to know why he has been writing such distortions of the truth.  I also demanded of him the location of The Arch Druid Aeaden that I have been tasked with finding.  He denied any knowledge of the Location of the Arch Druid.  I believe his word when he said he did not know for I could hear the notes of truth in his words.  I also detected the notes of truth and belief in what he has written of the Druid Nellen.  I have spoke to my friend the Arch Druidess Jaelynn and she has indicated to me that the Druid Nellen has great promise if he survives these dangerous lands.  I will have to make time to keep an eye on these two to make sure that the evil forces that roam the lands do not corrupt them.  Tomorrow I will continue my search for the Arch Druid Aeaden.  I fear that evil Forces have taken him.<br>
<br>
Rhapsodey stops writing as the sounds of battle come to her on the wind.  Her sensitive ears can pick out the cries for help.  She Quickly dons her armor and Grabs her weapons and follows the sounds of battle.  Shortly she arrives near the Great wooden bridge leading to the northern Karranas.  She can see one of the ancient hill giants attacking a group of adventures she can see a number of their members are already down and the rest will be shortly joining them.  Why must those stupid young fools attack him they should have run?  The Arch Druidess Jaelynn wont even attack him.  I should just let him kill them.  She turns to walk away. And stops after two steps.  Why Milady must I be so protective of fools as she turns and charges toward the battle.  She quickly closes the distance being careful to approach the giant from behind.  She swings her ancient magical mace at the back of the giant’s knee and she hits it with a solid crunch of breaking bone.  And then her ancient mace releases a blast of magical fire that Staggers the giant and causes it to turn on her.  It roars in pain and swings at her trying to rip her head from her shoulders.  She dodges the giant clumsy attack and watches as the party of young fools flee across the bridge.  Well Rhapsodey what are we going to do now.  If this big fool hits me it will be all over.  In her moment of distraction she fails to notice the other massive fist coming at her right side and it connects with the shattering crash of buckling armor and breaking bones.  The brutal impact throws her body into the river.  The hill giant quickly stomps into the river to recover his dinner but to his disgust the current has taken the body and he cannot find it.  He eventually wanders off in search of a new dinner of adventurers.  A short time after the giant departs from the area a form raises from the water and slowly and painfully drags itself under the foot of the bridge.  There the form collapses and does not move again.  <br>
