   I, Reoki K’vatra, a shaman of great standing among my tribe, have been called upon a great quest for knowledge.  To gain the knowledge I seek I had to leave my favored hunting grounds of the glorious mountains of the Everfrost Peaks. <br>
   In my many travels I have met many.   One of the ones I have met in passing is a young bard.  She is quite pretty in her strange looking way.  She is so tiny to me that I have been afraid to touch her without hurting her.  She claims to be wood elf……   I have heard of such beings but never thought that I would meet one.  Over my travels I have passed ways with her many times, and of course we have become friends over the course of time.<br>
    <br>
<br>
    Well, enough of remincing.  I have far to go this day.  I am heading to go back home to tell my tribe of some of the wonders I have seen.  It’s a long journey from High Hold Keep. <br>
    As I leav the pass from High Hold Keep I hear a Roar of anger and victory.  It doesn’t sound like it came from a natural throat, but as if it came from the Gods.  Thinking to my self,” Oh, No.  It must be a giant.  Hmmmm I don’t have the strength to meddle with one of those evil beings.  But, I can not leave those whom it will harm to die alone. “<br>
    Sigh.  Hear I came to help another hapless person who doesn’t know when to flee when the fleeing is good.  Ohh well, that is the life of a shaman.<br>
     As I get nearer I see a group of adventurers hounding this giant.  Then as I start to head their way to help those I see laying on the ground, I see a person sneaking up behind the giant.  I lose sight of what happens then because I have my hands full keeping a warrior, who’s ribs are broken and who is bleeding all of his life’s blood on the ground, alive.<br>
    Praying to the spirits,” Please Oh Great Spirits, fill this brave and courageous warrior the strength and vitality of your will.”   As soon as I finish praying he starts to breathe again, and the blood loss has stopped.  “Thank You, Oh Great Spirits for you favor.”<br>
<br>
    I finally start to look around puzzled.  All of this warriors companions have left him for dead, and the giant has left too.  With this turn of events I grow very wary and concerned.  Looking around al I see is a vast plain.  Way off in the distance I can see a bridge.  Then, I hear a roar of disappointment.  Looking closer I see a giant thrashing in the water looking for something.  Hoping to my self that all got a way.  Eventually the giant gives up his search.  <br>
    I hide the warrior I saved in a dense thicket.  He should be fine here.  He will be waking up soon, and then he can find his comrades.  <br>
    I then start heading to the area that the giant left hoping to find what ever had his interest.   When I get to the bank of the river, I see where the giant had torn up the bank.  But, what is this???   I see a blood trail.  Following this bloody trail to the footing of the bridge what do I find?  “Oh Great Spirits hear my call.  Please bring Rhapsodey back from the brink of death.  Do not let her pass the final veil,” this I pray with all of my might.  <br>
    For hear underneath the bridge lies the bashed and battered body of my dear little fragile little bard.  “Oh please don’t leave me my friend. “ I mutter under my breath.  “Spirits IF you never grant me your favor again, Please, OH Please, don’t let my friend die.  Please don’t let her be harmed.”   <br>
    As I cry over my friend a blue nimbus starts to surround her.  All of the sudden she starts to cough.  Tears of joy start to stream down my face.  “Thank You.  Thank You Great Spirits.  I reaffirm my ties with you,” I cry out with over whealming happiness.  <br>
   When Rhapsodey awakes I take her in my arms.  She is so tiny; I could hold her up in one hand. <br>
    “Well, my friend are you feeling alright?”  I ask.  <br>
    She says,” Yes, But will you please remind me next time I see an idiot trying to kill a giant to head the other way?”<br>
    “Sure.  But, I can only do so if we travel together.”  I state.  “ Would you mind seeing this great world with me?”<br>
    Of course you all know how she answered, because we are still hunting and learning about this great world together.<br>
